  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Heaven And Earth
---
Yao said, "Many sons mean many fears. Riches mean many troubles. Long
life means many shames. These three are of no use in nourishing Virtue
- therefore I decline them."
